The paper deals with an algorithmic problem in integer linear programming, which is a fundamental topic in computer science. The paper's focus on a reduction to the Vector Domination problem suggests that it may belong to the Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) or Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper's use of exponential time complexity suggests that it may belong to the Computational Complexity (cs.CC) sub-category. The problem's combinatorial nature and the use of algorithms suggest that it may also belong to the Computational Geometry (cs.CG) or Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories.
